<font color="#FF0000">REPLIES TO JOE &amp; PETE</font><br>
<tt>Mon Jan 20 15:25:53 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
1.To Joe: Not having any national stats to go on, I can't prove from my own experience that Vietnam Vets' suicides are less than non-vets of the same age bracket. Most of the ones I know of are within the last 5 years, after years of struggle with personal ghosts and demons and chronic illness and/or reduced function due to injury, some of it war related. I would not be surprised if the data you cite is several years old, and that the suicide rate has risen again. <br><br>
2.To Pete: For three years, we have processed over 300 homeless veterans at the Philadelphia Standdown. Every one is verified on site by the VA or not allowed in. The repeat percentage from year to year is about 15 to 20%. One note- Two thirds of our tent leaders the second year were homeless the first year. <br>

<p><code>-- turtle@plantaganet.com  (Gerald Alan Ney) </code><p>


